Omnia eMeter
If your
meter is located inside or outside the house
Eltel will contact you well in advance of the meter change and inform you of an approximate time slot for the change.
A few weeks prior to the meter change, Eltel will be in touch with a booking proposal. If the proposed time DOESN’T suit you contact Eltel’s customer service and change to your preferred time and date.
For Business
How
well in advance you will receive information about time and date for your
change, and how specific this information is, depends on where your meter is
located. If it is
located indoors, we might need your help to reach it. In that case, you will be
appointed to a time and date for the change. If it is located outdoors, or in a
central location in the property, for example in a multi-occupied building,
Eltel will handle the replacement, and you will receive an approximate date of
when the change will take place.
Please make sure that the installer has free access to the meter. A person aged 18 or older needs to be present as the change takes place.
Eltel execute
the meter change
Prior to
our visit, please clean up any items that might obscure the meter. This allows
for a smooth change.
If you have
your own equipment connected to the meter, the functions of that equipment will
be erased with the meter change.
Your new meter is now in place, and you have access to new and smart functionality! The old electricity meter will be recycled.
The installer from Eltel is able to present identification with a certificate of competence. As the change takes place, the electricity will be switched off for about 15-20 minutes. The installer documents both your old and your new meter registration and reports back to us at Göteborg Energi.
When the
installer replaces your meter, the electricity will be switched off for about
15-20 minutes. This might affect the lift, utility room, internet connection
and other functions dependent on electricity.
If
your meter is located inside your house, you, or a person aged 18 or older,
need to be at home for the change. You or that person need to be able to show
the installer where the electricity meter is located.
How the change is carried out
The company
Eltel will execute the actual electricity meter change. Therefore, they are the
ones who will be in touch with more detailed information as the meter change in
your household approaches.
Please
note!
Starting in
autumn 2022 and until the end of 2024, we will replace all electricity meters
in Gothenburg. We start in Kvillebäcken and will then gradually speed up the
rollout. You will of course be notified on beforehand before we visit you.
