Our new electricity meter
Safer
delivery with the new electricity meter
Customer
interface
If you
would like to purchase hardware from a service provider in order to connect
with the installed OMNIA eMeter, please keep in mind that it should comply with
the standard that our electricity meters are based on. It is advisable to be
attentive to that certain electricity grid suppliers have chosen a different
standard, one that is developed for the Norwegian market where the HAN-port has
a RJ45 switch, and that certain hardware is developed to suit exactly that
version.
Our
– and your – new electricity meter is called OMNIA eMeter and is delivered by
Kamstrup. It will increase the amount of reading data and the number of
parameters that we measure in addition to your electricity consumption.
Do you have
any questions regarding your new electricity meter or the customer interface?
OMNIA
e-Meter is well prepared for metering production, something that is necessary
if you, for instance, install solar panels. We will also measure voltage in the
mains power source, which will give us the prerequisites to be more proactive and sort out
faults before they affect you as a customer.
. The customer interface is
based on the Dutch standard DSMR with a RJ12 switch and it complies with the
business recommendations as stated by Swedenergy (Energiföretagen Sverige).
The upside
with an open customer interface is that your electricity meter registers more
data than just your consumption, something that you gain access to when
connecting with the customer interface. It enables you to follow and analyse
your electricity consumption. With hardware that you connect with the customer
interface, you could, for example, direct the heating of your property or the
charging of an electric car.
The
biggest change when switching to OMNIA eMeter is that it has an open interface,
a customer port, also called


